The paper presents a hierarchical multitask framework based on Planning as Inference, which involves learning options for different tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions that the framework can be applied to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks, which further supports these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves learning policies and terminations for options, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
